To install Docker on your MacBook via the terminal, follow these steps:

Step 1: Install Homebrew (If Not Already Installed)
Homebrew is a package manager for macOS, which simplifies the installation process.

Open the Terminal.
Run the following command to install Homebrew:
bash
Copy code
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
After installation, ensure Homebrew is up-to-date:
bash
Copy code
brew update
Step 2: Install Docker Using Homebrew
Install Docker:
bash
Copy code
brew install --cask docker
This will download and install Docker Desktop.
Step 3: Start Docker Desktop
After installation, start Docker Desktop:
bash
Copy code
open /Applications/Docker.app
Follow the setup instructions in Docker Desktop.
Step 4: Verify Installation
Open the Terminal.
Check the Docker version:
bash
Copy code
docker --version
Run a test container:
bash
Copy code
docker run hello-world
Step 5: (Optional) Install Docker CLI Tools
To ensure Docker CLI tools work correctly:

Link Docker CLI to your shell:
bash
Copy code
ln -s /Applications/Docker.app/Contents/Resources/bin/docker /usr/local/bin/docker
